<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-15T21:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-15T21:34:00-05:00" n="735" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2641: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-16T11:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">August 16,
                                        1922—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 17—4:30
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Recent mutiny Chinese troops Pokotu reported by Stevens and hold up of
                            train by Russian brigands ample proof Chinese soldiers unable guard
                            adequately Chinese Eastern Railway.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>